PPS - be sure to keep us updated on your epic status and any help you need.  You know we'll all be there! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udamanields.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damaniel DS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#0000FF>(3/28/02 12:55:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tactics and strategy in Hate</span><hr size=1> Yanda,, Grats on the Pants =), I'm sorry I had to go to work and missed them.. <br>
<br>
People always ask me why I use Celestial heal.. They say its a waste of mana.. I say That when I cast a Celestial on Dinekus or Ramune when I am in the pull group Saves My arse till they can gain enough aggro for me to Complete heal... Not to mention,, Un mezzed mobs do not Look at Celestial as a  threat... I mean,, when Dink has 2 Bubbs of health left,, he still has 2k + Hp's... Keeping him Alive with a Celestial for 24 seconds.. (and the chanter) while the mobs become under control is an ounce of prevention to me =).. And I can do what I do Best when its over,, Meditate heh...<br>
