Dragonslayers</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/udamanields.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damaniel DS</A> at: 3/28/02 1:08:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uyandapanacea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yanda Panacea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#0000FF>(4/1/02 1:31:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tactics and strategy in Hate</span><hr size=1> I totally agree with your comments about celestial healing.  It is always the first spell I cast, even when about to complete heal the tank, because it can help keep them alive during the looonnnngggg casting time for complete heal.  LOL   It does seem to aggro some mobs, have not really had time to notice which ones, though.  But I have definitely been aggroed because of casting celestial healing.  Great idea about the epic and I will be sure to find out when you are planning to do it and I will for sure try to make it on to help you out.  Thanks for all the great suggestions, and I like the &quot;root&quot; plan, let's try it next time to see if it helps, hehe.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uneaadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neaadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#0000FF>(4/2/02 10:54:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.swbell.net/lhays/tun_me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tactics and 